channel.title: msnbc.com: Top msnbc.com headlines
channel.description: Msnbc.com is a leader in breaking news and original journalism.

item.title: Couple crashes Obama state dinner
item.description: Two aspiring reality-TV stars appear to have crashed the White House's state dinner, penetrating security to mingle with the likes of Joe Biden and Rahm Emanuel.

item.title: Day of the super-turkey could be nigh
item.description: Genetic research by Virginia Tech scientists could lead to 'happier,' plumper, tastier birds.

item.title: President vs. party on troop increase
item.description: President's speech at West Point next week will outline his new war strategy, but his most skeptical audience will be on Capitol Hill.

item.title: Black Friday deals? Socks, diapers
item.description: As stores prepare for hordes of Black Friday shoppers and mark down high-definition TVs and hot toys, they're also pushing deals on necessities like socks and diapers.

item.title: Commandos, candles as Mumbai marks attacks
item.description: Black-clad commandos rappelled down a building and Mumbai's police showed off their new gear a year after a terror attack across the city killed 166 people.

item.title: China announces plan to boost energy efficiency
item.description: China announced plans Thursday to drastically boost its energy efficiency as part of its contribution to the fight against global warming.

item.title: Man dies after day stuck upside-down in cave
item.description: A man stuck upside-down in a cave for more than a day died early Thursday, despite the efforts of dozens of rescuers, authorities said.

item.title: Philippine massacre suspect surrenders
item.description: Authorities say a scion of a powerful clan suspected in the massacre of 57 people in an election caravan in the southern Philippines has turned himself in.

item.title: Salvation Army kettles take plastic
item.description: There could be less jingle in the Salvation's Army's hallmark red kettles this season. The charity is testing kettles that take debit and credit cards.

item.title: Opinion: Lions here to stay on Thanksgiving
item.description: Pompei: Having the Lions play on Thanksgiving is as much a part of the holiday as a good afternoon snooze. And they sometimes go together. But that doesn’t mean the Lions will be knocked off their Thanksgiving perch anytime soon. The league — or most of it — appears to value the tradition that goes along with having the Lions and Cowboys play on Thanksgiving.

media:content.media:description: From the Kentucky Derby hat parade to Thanksgiving football games, take a look at some of the best traditions in sports.

item.title: Arsenal found at ex-doctor's Ohio apartment
item.description: About 35 pipe bombs, an assortment of firearms, hundreds of rounds of ammunition were found in a former doctor's apartment following two loud explosions, police say.

item.title: Sponsored By:
10-time All-Star Iverson reportedly will retire
item.description: With no apparent interest from NBA teams, Allen Iverson is set to retire, according to an online report, which said Iverson plans to retire but also that “I feel strongly that I can still compete at the highest level.”

media:content.media:description: Slideshow: Images from one of the most controversial, and talented players in NBA history.

item.title: Rains soak pilgrims at Islam’s hajj
item.description: Muslim pilgrims circle Islam's holiest site, the Kaaba, in traditional white robes, with new additions — umbrellas and face masks — at the opening of the annual hajj.

item.title: Sponsored By:
No. 5 Kentucky survives OT scare from Stanford
item.description: Freshman sensation John Wall scored a season-best 23 points, including clutch shots in the final minute that sent the game to overtime, and No. 5 Kentucky closed with an eight-point run for a 73-65 victory over gritty Stanford on Wednesday night in the championship game of the Cancun Challenge at the Moon Palace Resort.

item.title: More stay home for Thanksgiving
item.description: Millions of Americans are spending the holiday at home, saying the poor economy has made it unaffordable to hit the road or board a plane.

media:content.media:description: Millions of Americans have taken to the roads and skies. While planes are full and more people are driving, all indications point to travelers showing up for turkey dinner on time.

item.title: Chinese magazine reports on secret jails
item.description: A state-run magazine reveals a system of secret detention centers where Chinese citizens are forcibly held to prevent them from lodging formal complaints with the central government.

item.title: Nets drop to 0-15, are 2 losses from record
item.description: The New Jersey Nets moved a loss closer to the record for the NBA’s worst start to a season on Wednesday night when they dropped their 15th straight game, 93-83 to the Portland Trail Blazers.

item.title: Military families united by tragedies
item.description: The mother of a suicidal Marine wants to share Thanksgiving with the wife of a vet charged with murder. They share a belief that the military doesn't look after its members once they return from war.

item.title: Fertility treatment may mean fewer baby boys
item.description: The number of baby boys conceived by a fertility treatment known as ICSI may be lower than what is produced by Mother Nature, a new study suggests.

item.title: U.S. sets new climate target
item.description: President Obama will attend the U.N. climate summit next month in Denmark, taking with him a pledge to reduce U.S. greenhouse gas emissions by 17 percent by 2020, the White House says.

item.title: ‘Princess and the Frog’ is a hearty hop
item.description: The movie isn't the second coming of "Beauty and the Beast" or "The Lion King." It's just plain pleasant, an old-fashioned little charmer that's not straining to be the next glib animated compendium of pop-culture flotsam.

item.title: How Twitter can help you save on travel
item.description: Twitter isn't just a networking site, it's a powerful tool that can save you money and change how you plan your travels.

item.title: Top 10 Black Friday Web sites
item.description: Here's a list of Web sites you'll want to keep an eye on for Black Friday deals, so sync them across your computers with Chrome bookmarks, save them to delicious or just store them in your favorite browser.
